26 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "homestead vendor" means a
27 person:
28 (1) that prepares and sells food products from the person's
29 property; and
30 (2) from which not more than one million five hundred
31 thousand dollars ($1,500,000) in gross sales is received in a
32 single year.
33 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "meat product" means a product
34 capable of use as human food that is made wholly or in part from
35 meat or other parts of the carcass of any of the following:
36 (1) Cattle.
37 (2) Sheep.
38 (3) Swine.
39 (4) Bison.
40 (5) Poultry.
41 (6) Goats.
42 (7) Rabbit.
