1 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "produce" means any
2 agricultural or naturally occurring product that is:
3 (1) grown, cultivated, raised, or harvested for human
4 consumption; and
5 (2) not prohibited by state or federal law.
6 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "small farm" means land:
7 (1) that is used for growing crops or raising livestock;
8 (2) from which a person prepares and sells food products; and
9 (3) from which not more than one million five hundred
10 thousand dollars ($1,500,000) in gross sales is received from:
11 (A) livestock products;
12 (B) cultivated or harvested crops; or
13 (C) the sale of food products;
14 in a single year.
15 Sec. 5. The state department, a local unit of government (as
16 defined in IC 14-22-31.5-1), the corporation, or a local health
17 department may not impose any rules, regulations, certifications,
18 or licensing requirements on a:
19 (1) homestead vendor; or
20 (2) small farm;
21 that are not required under federal law.
22 Sec. 6. A homestead vendor or the owner of a small farm may
23 sell the following items on the homestead or small farm's premises:
24 (1) Meat products:
25 (A) raised at the individual's primary residence; and
26 (B) slaughtered, processed, and labeled in compliance with
27 IC 15-17-5.
28 (2) Prepared foods, including baked goods.
29 (3) Candy.
30 (4) Produce.
31 (5) Natural sweeteners.
32 (6) Fruit spreads.
33 Sec. 7. (a) A homestead vendor or the owner of a small farm
34 shall include a label for packaged homemade food products or a
35 sign for unpackaged homemade food products that contains the
36 following information:
37 (1) The name of the homestead vendor or the owner of the
38 small farm that produced the homemade food product.
39 (2) The address of the homestead vendor or the owner of the
40 small farm that produced the homemade food product.
41 (3) The ingredients of the homemade food product, in
42 descending order by predominance by weight.
HB 1424—LS 7092/DI 150

8
1 (4) A description of the homemade food product.
2 (5) A description of allergens that might have come in contact
3 with the homemade food product.
4 (6) The following statement in at least 10 point type: "This
5 product was produced by a homestead vendor or the owner of
6 a small farm that is exempt from government licensing and
7 inspection.".
8 (b) A homestead vendor may not ship or deliver a food product
9 to an end consumer who is located outside Indiana.
10 Sec. 8. A homestead vendor or the owner of a small farm who
11 sells meat products from livestock under this chapter must keep
12 the meat products refrigerated in a manner consistent with best
13 food handling practices.
